JD Wetherspoon Says Comparable Sales Rise 2.3% Over First Half

-- B y   C o l m   H e a t l e y
-- 
2011-03-11T07:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/jd-wetherspoon-says-comparable-sales-rise-2-3-over-first-half.html
  JD Wetherspoon Plc (JDW)  said comparable
sales rose by 2.3 percent over the 26-week first-half period to
Jan. 23.  Total sales, including new pubs, increased by 7.6 percent
to 525.4 million pounds, the company said in a statement today.
Kirk Davis has been named finance director, Wetherspoon said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
